[Gemini]: This is a classic Time-of-check Time-of-use (TOCTOU) race condition. The code first checks if the lock file exists (`if not Path(self.lock_file).exists():`) and then, in a separate operation, opens it (`os.open(...)`). An attacker could create a file (such as a symbolic link to a sensitive file) between these two operations. Since `os.O_TRUNC` is used, this could lead to the truncation of the linked file. The fix is to use `os.O_CREAT | os.O_EXCL` to perform an atomic "create if not exists" operation. This is a true positive.

